content.description: Crack climb, stand start with finger lock and sloping rail climb up the crack to a good pocket hold and gun for the top to a sloping jug mantle
content.location: Just before "tight and light" follow a trail right (east) till you come to a 20' tall granite wall. Get to the top of the wall by going to the right or left side of it. The boulder sits on the top of the wall roughly in the middle.

content.description: Stand start at flaring crack/seam. A couple moves will put you at jug, match then move up and onto slab. Climbs more like a face than a crack
content.location: From Hardened Criminal head up trail, at top of short hill/ slab look right to a small tunnel between two boulders. Go through tunnel, look for crack on the left.

content.description: Stand start and work up undercling to the right then climb up through cracks to reach the top.
content.location: From red stagger continue on the trial heading up hill (trail goes by the right side of the komodo boulder)

content.description: Sit start at jug with shelf behind you, climb using jugs, cracks and ledges to wiggle through a O/W-ish channel to reach the top.
content.location: If standing and facing All I Can go right in between the two boulders, once you come out the other side youll see it on the left.

content.description: Sit start on low flat edges down left. Head up and right through hallway on rails and low feet to exit and top out at end of tunnel.  Quality boulder problem with unfortunate key feet that continue to crumble a little
content.location: From the Hardened Criminal boulder continue through hallway and up trail above slabs. About 200' up and left will be the "railway tunnel" on your left. Here lies the problem.

content.description: Stand start in the middle of the boulder, start holding tooth looking feature and climb straight up.
content.location: Standing and facing Beginners Luck look left and youll see the boulder.

content.description: Starting on left side of the merging two cracks, work through a series of O/W and hand cracks to reach the top.
content.location: While on the central oaks trail go through underpass then look up and right.

content.description: Stand start at face high crimps just under dike, work up and left on crimps. Top out at  scoop at the lip.
content.location: From death row go left on the trail through the rock hallway

content.description: Sit start under the short prow with a right hand on a sloping scoop, left hand on the left wall. Squeeze with legs to make moves up then left to jugs up towards the top
content.location: short atari-like prow. This boulder is best found by heading up trail from Hardened Criminal then looking right to a small "tunnel" between two boulders. Go through tunnel, boulder is on your right, opposite a crack/seam

content.description: When facing simple man climb left arête. Sit start with left hand on arete and right hand on low pinch/crimp.
Stand Start using edges and stemming feet, once high enough reach right hand out to crack/pocket and reach for left arête, head up to scoop and top out.
content.location: When facing simple man go right and over the small hill then youll see the U-shaped boulder on the other side.

content.description: Stand start on small cheat stone with right hand on high rail and work up arête.
content.location: To the left of Undercover on the same boulder.

content.description: Very fun, super secure chimney with an exciting top out. A little highball but very secure the whole way.
content.location: Close to Simple Man, it's slightly hidden behind a tree.
From All I Can follow trail up hill up and around to the back side of the same boulder (Beginners Luck is the same crack as All I Can but just on the other side of the boulder)

content.description: A short wide-hands crack leads to a cool, inobvious topout on slopers.
content.location: Just east of the Missing Link and Red Stagger. Right next to Squamish Finger.
